OL,3,CMan jailed for murder he committed two
OL,4,Cdays after prison release
OL,6,F"Today, justice has been served on
OL,7,FOwen Blades. Our brother John did not
OL,8,Fdeserve to die in the cruel the way he
OL,9,Fdid. He was in his own home; that was
OL,10,Fsupposed to be his safe space, anyone
OL,11,Fshould feel safe in their own home,
OL,12,Fand no one has the right to invade it
OL,13,Flike that. We can't imagine how
OL,14,Fterrified he would have been.
OL,16,F"On 2 February this year, John would
OL,17,Fhave been 70. Instead of celebrating
OL,18,Fhis birthday, we had to take flowers
OL,19,Fto his grave. We never envisaged that
OL,20,Fwe would be doing this.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/7
